commitResults.messageTitle: Modify edit command to edit patient status and ward
commitResults.messageBody:
The existing AB3 edit command only allows editing entry names.

As any patient management system will need to be able to perform
frequent updations of patient status and ward, let's modify this.

Now, patient name and nric will not be editable (as these are
identifying information, whose updation would be better met by
deleting and re-entering as a new patient). Instead, only patient
status and ward will be editable.

Modify addward command to take in capacity
commitResults.messageBody:
Previously, addward would only initialize wards by name and default
capacity of 10.
Also, it used the ward prefix rather than the name prefix.

Let's:
- change the command prefix from "w/" to "name/" for ward name
- add command prefix of "c/" for ward capacity
- add validation for ward capacity (integer within a reasonable range)
